
// This Hyperlambda code executes a workflow action named "markdown2html" using the [execute] slot. It specifies a file path for the action and passes in arguments, where the "markdown" argument is dynamically retrieved and encoded from a specified content node. The code effectively converts Markdown content into HTML by executing the specified workflow action.
execute:magic.workflows.actions.execute
   name:markdown2html
   filename:/misc/workflows/actions/misc/markdown2html.hl
   arguments
      markdown:x:--/execute/=html-encode-body/*/content
